#
# Identifier-redaction goldens (ADR-0010). Each SQL string is parsed under the M1
# superset (PostgreSQL) and rendered in Canonical and Redacted modes. The redacted
# block proves no original identifier text survives: simple, qualified (per dotted
# part), and keyword-as-identifier names all collapse to the `id` placeholder and
# literals to `?`, while keywords, operators, punctuation, and qualified-name arity
# remain. Quoted-identifier masking (every quote style) is proven at the render
# layer by the squonk-ast render unit tests; the M1 parser does not yet accept
# quoted identifiers, so it cannot be exercised end-to-end here. The SQL strings
# are hand-authored for this repository; the expected blocks are generated.
# Rewrite with:
#   REWRITE=1 cargo test -p squonk-conformance goldens::tests::datadriven_golden_corpus --lib

